# Rules vs Skills

**Rules** (`.cursor/rules/`) — coding conventions auto-attached by file glob. Follow them when editing matching files.

**Skills** (`.cursor/skills/`) — on-demand workflows. Invoke by name when doing that task.

| Task | Use |
|------|-----|
| Edit components, lib, app routes | Matching rule (conventions) |
| Write new tests | `writing-tests` skill + `vitest-unit-testing` rule |
| Verify UI after changes | `verifying-in-browser` skill |
| Type-check after edits | `auto-type-checking` skill |
| Performance audit | `auditing-performance` skill |
| Open a pull request | `creating-pr` skill |
| Debug dev server / test crashes | `monitoring-terminal-errors` skill |

Do not duplicate rule content inside skills — reference the rule instead.
